1. Motivation

(\(F\):cdf) \(X_1,\ldots,X_n\) . .

.

. \(F\) \(\hat F\) .

\(\hat F\) , , . \(\hat F\) \(X_1,\ldots,X_n\) \(n\) (\(X_1^\ast,\ldots,X_n^\ast\)).

2. Plug-in estimator

\(F\) functional . ,

  • moment

\[\mu_k(F)=\int x^k dF(x)\]

  • central moment

\[\omega_k(F)=\int (x-\mu_1(F))^k dF(x)\]

  • \(p\)-th quantile

\[\xi_p(F)=\inf\{ x:F(x) \geq p \}\]

.

(EDF:empirical distribution function) \(\hat F_n(x)=(1/n)\sum_{i=1}^n I(X_i \leq x)\) \(F\) ,

\[\hat\mu_k(F)=\mu_k(\hat F_n)=\int x^k d\hat F_n(x)=(1/n)\sum_{i=1}^n X_i^k\] \[\hat\omega_k(F)=\omega_k(\hat F_n)=\int (x-\mu_1(\hat F_n))^k d\hat F_n(x)=(1/n)\sum_{i=1}^n (X_i - \bar X)^k\] \[\hat\xi_p(F)=\xi_p(\hat F_n)=\inf\{ x:\hat F_n(x) \geq p \}\]

.

3. Applications

3.1 Estimation of variance

. .

. \(\sigma^2/n\) \(\sigma^2\) MLE . , . .

(\(m\)) .

\[var(m)\approx \frac{1}{4nf(\xi_{0.5})},~f:density\]

. \(f\) .

. .

, \(B\) . \(X^\ast_b = (X_{b1}^\ast,\ldots,X_{bn}^\ast),~b=1,\ldots,B\) , \(m_b^\ast\) . \(B\) . ,

\[\hat{var}(m)^\ast = \frac{1}{B}\sum_{b=1}^B\left(m_b^\ast - \frac{1}{B}\sum_{i=1}^Bm_b^\ast\right)^2\]

. \(m_b^\ast\) (Bootstrap estimator) .

\(\theta(F)\) \(T(X)\) .

\[\hat{var}(T(X))^\ast = \frac{1}{B}\sum_{b=1}^B\left(T(X^\ast_b) - \frac{1}{B}\sum_{i=1}^BT(X^\ast_b)\right)^2\]

\(T(X^\ast_b)\) \(b\) .

3.2 Bias-reduction

.

\[\hat{bias}(T(X))^\ast = \frac{1}{B}\sum_{b=1}^B T(X^\ast_b) - \theta(\hat F_n)\]

\(\theta(\hat F_n)\) \(T(X)\) .

,

\[T(X)-\hat{bias}(T(X))^\ast = 2T(X) - \frac{1}{B}\sum_{b=1}^B T(X^\ast_b)\]

4.1 \(X_i\) follows the Exponential distribution with mean 10. Target : mean

10 \(n=20\) , . .

  1. \(\bar X \sim \Gamma(n,\mu/n)\) .
  2. CLT . , \(\bar X \sim N(\mu,\mu^2/n)\).
  3. . , \(\bar x\) .
  4. CLT \(\bar X \sim N(\mu,\sigma^2/n)\).
  5. () . , \(\hat F_n\) .
n=20
B=5000
set.seed(1)
x=rexp(n,1/10);barx=mean(x);sx=sd(x)
bmp=bm=c()
xbp=xb=matrix(0,B,n)
for (i in 1:B)
    {
    xb[i,]=sample(x,replace=TRUE)
    bm[i]=mean(xb[i,])
    xbp[i,]=rexp(n,1/mean(x))
    bmp[i]=mean(xbp[i,])
    }
plot(density(bm),main="",xlab="",ylab="",lwd=2,ylim=c(0,0.2))
lines(seq(0,150,0.01),dgamma(seq(0,150,0.01),shape=n,scale=10/n),lwd=2,lty=2,col=2)
lines(seq(0,150,0.01),dgamma(seq(0,150,0.01),shape=n,scale=mean(x)/n),lwd=2,lty=3,col=3)
lines(seq(0,150,0.01),dnorm(seq(0,150,0.01),mean(x),sqrt(var(x)/n)),lwd=2,lty=4,col=4)
lines(density(bmp),lwd=2,col=5)
legend(13,0.2,c("TRUE","Estimated gamma","Normal approximation","Bootstrap","Para-Bootstrap"),col=c(2,3,4,1,5),lty=c(2,3,4,1,5),lwd=2)

\(M=1000\) , .

n=20
B=5000;M=1000
set.seed(1)
EG=CLTE=PB=PB_P=CLT=NB=NB_P=matrix(0,M,2)
for (j in 1:M)
{
x=rexp(n,1/10);barx=mean(x);sx=sd(x)
bmp=bm=c()
xbp=xb=matrix(0,B,n)
for (i in 1:B)
    {
    xb[i,]=sample(x,replace=TRUE)
    bm[i]=mean(xb[i,])
    xbp[i,]=rexp(n,1/mean(x))
    bmp[i]=mean(xbp[i,])
}
EG[j,]=c(barx/qgamma(0.975,shape=length(x),scale=1/length(x)),barx/qgamma(0.025,shape=length(x),scale=1/length(x)))
CLTE[j,]=c(barx-qnorm(0.975)*barx/sqrt(length(x)),barx+qnorm(0.975)*barx/sqrt(length(x)))
PB[j,]=c(2*barx-quantile(bmp,0.975),2*barx-quantile(bmp,0.025))
PB_P[j,]=c(quantile(bmp,0.025),quantile(bmp,0.975))
## CLT
CLT[j,]=c(barx-qnorm(0.975)*sx/sqrt(length(x)),barx+qnorm(0.975)*sx/sqrt(length(x)))
## Nonpara-Boot
NB[j,]=c(2*barx-quantile(bm,0.975),2*barx-quantile(bm,0.025))
NB_P[j,]=c(quantile(bm,0.025),quantile(bm,0.975))
}
# average lengths of intervals
c(diff(colMeans(EG)),diff(colMeans(CLTE)),diff(colMeans(PB)),diff(colMeans(PB_P)),diff(colMeans(CLT)),diff(colMeans(NB)),diff(colMeans(NB_P)))
## [1] 9.678992 8.809220 8.775314 8.775314 8.499464 8.210213 8.210213
# coverage proportions
c(mean(apply(EG-10,1,prod)<0),mean(apply(CLTE-10,1,prod)<0),mean(apply(PB-10,1,prod)<0),mean(apply(PB_P-10,1,prod)<0),mean(apply(CLT-10,1,prod)<0),mean(apply(NB-10,1,prod)<0),mean(apply(NB_P-10,1,prod)<0))
## [1] 0.937 0.921 0.901 0.929 0.902 0.887 0.897
